s for the Assessment of Bilinguals presents innovative solutions for the evaluation of language abilities and proficiency in multilingual speakers – and by extension, the evaluation of their cognitive and academic abilities. This volume brings together researchers working in a variety of bilingual settings to discuss critical matters central to the assessment of bilingual children and adults. The studies include typically developing bilingual children, bilingual children who may be at risk for language impairments, bilingual and multilingual children and adults found in classrooms, and second-language learners in childhood and adulthood. The contributions propose a variety of ways of assessing performance and abilities in the face of the multiple issues that complicate the best interpretation of test performance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEducation, BilingualxAbility testing. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aLanguage and languagesxAbility testing. 0aLanguage artsxAbility testing. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAlmgren, Margareta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarnes, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarreña, Andoni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBedore, Lisa M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErdos, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEzeizabarrena, Maria-José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiestas, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Iñaki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGathercole, Virginia C. Mueller, econtributor.4ctb